quran[49]{c,v,t}:
  43,57,"And when the son of Mary (Jesus) was given as an example, your people turned away from it (laughing and shouting)"
  43,58,"And they said: are our gods better or is he? They only gave you (this example) to argue. No, but they are argumentative people"
  43,59,He (Jesus) was only a servant whom We favored upon him and We made him an example for children of Israel
  43,60,"And if We wanted, We would have made some of you angels on the earth, to succeed you"
  43,61,"And it is certainly an indication of the hour, so do not doubt it, and follow Me. This is a straight path"
  43,62,"And do not let Satan hold you up, as he is indeed your clear enemy"
  43,63,"And when Jesus brought the clear proofs, he said: I have certainly brought you the wisdom to clarify for you some of that which you disagree about it, so be cautious of God and obey me"
  43,64,"Indeed God is He who is my Master and your Master, so serve Him. This is a straight path"
  43,65,"But the parties disagreed among themselves, so woe to those who did wrong from punishment of a painful day"
  43,66,"Do they wait (for anything) except the hour to come to them suddenly, while they do not realize"
  43,67,"On that day, the friends are enemy of each other except those who controlled themselves"
  43,68,"My servants, there is no fear for you today, and you will not be sad"
  43,69,Those who believed in Our signs and were submitted
  43,70,"you and your spouses enter the garden, being delighted"
  43,71,"Golden plates and drinking glasses are circulated for them, and whatever the soul desires and pleases the eyes is in there, and you remain in it forever"
  43,72,And this is the garden that you are made to inherit because of what you were doing
  43,73,There are plenty of fruits for you to eat in it
  43,74,Indeed the guilty ones remain in the punishment of hell forever
  43,75,It is not reduced for them and they are hopeless in it
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but they were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"And they call out: master (of hell), have your Master finish us off. He says: indeed you are staying"
  43,78,"We have certainly brought you the truth, but most of you dislike the truth"
  43,79,"Or did they firmly settle on an issue, then indeed We are firmly settled too"
  43,80,"Or do they think that We do not hear their secret and their whisper? Yes (We hear them), and Our messengers are with them writing"
  43,81,"Say: if there was a child for the beneficent, then I would be the first of the servants"
  43,82,"Master of the skies and the earth, Master of the throne is flawless (and beyond) what they describe"
  43,83,So leave them talk uselessly and play until they meet their day which they are promised
  43,84,"And He is the One who is god in the skies and god in the earth, and He is the wise, the knowledgeable"
  43,85,"And blessed is the One that the rule of the skies and the earth and whatever between them belongs to Him, and the knowledge of the hour is with Him, and you are returned to Him"
  43,86,"And those you call on besides Him have no power of the mediation, except whoever testifies with the truth, and they know (the truth)"
  43,87,"And if you ask them who created them? They shall say: God. So how do they deviate"
  43,88,"And his saying was: my Master, indeed these people do not believe"
  43,89,"(God said:) so pardon/ignore them and say peace (and well-being), they will know"
  44,1,M. (Ha. Mim)
  44,2,By the clear (and clarifying) book
  44,3,"Indeed We revealed it in a blessed night, indeed We are warners"
  44,4,Every wise command is made distinct (and well defined) in it
  44,5,a command from Us. Indeed We are senders
  44,6,"A mercy from your Master. Indeed He hears all, knows all"
  44,7,"Master of the skies and the earth and whatever is between them, if you are certain"
  44,8,"There is no god except Him, He gives life and causes death, your Master and Master of your forefathers"
  44,9,"No, but they play around in doubt"
  44,10,So expect a day that the sky brings a visible smoke
  44,11,covering people. This is a painful punishment
  44,12,"Our Master, remove the punishment from us, indeed we are believers"
  44,13,"How is the reminder (of any use) for them, while a clarifying messenger has come to them"
  44,14,and they turned away from him and they said he is a mad man taught (by others)
  44,15,"We remove the punishment a little, (then) indeed you return (to disbelief)"
  44,16,"On a day that We assault with the great assault, indeed We take revenge"